  "footnotes": [
    {
      "id": "1",
      "text": "A program of study comprising subjects in the selected core areas and the computational concentration must be developed in consultation with the student’s doctoral thesis committee and approved by the CCSE graduate officer."
    },
    {
      "id": "2",
      "text": "Harvard course COMPSCI 2050 High Performance Computing for Science and Engineering is also an approved subject in this area."
    },
    {
      "id": "3",
      "text": "Students can also choose any 12-unit, letter-graded (not P/D/F), graduate-level Mathematics subject numbered 18.1* or higher not listed elsewhere in this approved subject list, though seminar and special tops subjects are generally not allowed."
    },
    {
      "id": "4",
      "text": "Subject to Sloan bidding process."
    }
  ],
